My favorite Thai place in SWFL! Every dish I have sampled here has been delicious, without exception. They serve up huge portions with fair prices for both lunch and dinner. Despite the unassuming location, the interior atmosphere and decor is tasteful, exotic, and romantic.  The service is flawless. Every member of the serving staff that I have interacted with over the years has been friendly and attentive. I've never run out of water and my food always comes out fast and fresh, even when they're extremely busy. I have never had a single complaint and every person I've ever brought here has loved their meal.  If you are a spicy food lover you need to try Thai! Siam Hut offers the option to customize your desired heat level. I order my food one level below the spiciness I want (usually hot) and ask for a side of chili oil so I can increase the intensity incrementally. It's a solid method that I recommend to everyone after once making the mistake of ordering a dish "Thai hot." It was one of only two dishes that has EVER been too spicy for me (and still I ate it, I just cried the whole time). If you have a more typical spice tolerance I would advise using this same strategy, but maybe ordering mild or medium to start and adjusting to taste from there.  Highly recommend trying the appetizer sampler & the red curry!

I have traveled the world and across the USA. Have frequened Thai restaurants all of my  adult life. This a very nicely decorated Thai place. With sweet people serving us. Unfortunately  the food was the worst ever. The dumplings were old and reheated, the Masaman Curry looked like it was thickened with some sort of thickening ingredient. I asked the waiter if the food had cornstarch and he asked another waiter, he came back and said no. We told him I have a severe reaction to corn. He walked away. 15 minutes after leaving the restaurant I had a corn reaction. Believe me I know what corn does to me. Have been sick all morning. My advice to this restaurant? Pay attention folks! You have lost me and my family as customers. I would have ordered another dish had I known you used cornstarch....which is usually never used in authentic Thai curries. The food was not good. Find a better chef, and be mindful of allergies and food sensitivities. This could have been a disaster if someone was allergic to peanuts and you did not disclose the ingredients after they asked. I am sure this was a very nice restaurant at one time.

Basically, this is Chinese food with curry paste, coconut milk and fish sauce instead of chicken stock, msg and cornstarch. Nice presentation, and a good break from American fare, though. Great food! Very attentive wait staff. Reasonable prices (~$10USD/plate). Excellent curries and Thai dishes. Don't be fooled by the exterior appearance inside is a authentic Thai experience. Loved it :)
Don't let the appearance fool you. This is good Thai food.
Great place! Don't let the outside fool you. Inside it's a cosy place that serves really good Thai food!

Great food, the Pad Thai and the Green Curry were well done and very flavorful. Really impressed with the Thai Toast as well as everything else in the Appetizer Combo. Had no problem placing the order and the food was ready when they said it would be. Curry was ordered to be Thai hot and had just the right level of heat without interfering with the flavor. Will definitely go back for more!
Extraordinary, we have eaten in hundreds of restaurants around the world this one is great

I LOVE their food. I have never been disappointed by the Pad Thai. Delicious!! However, they are very hard to get ahold of for calling in a to-go order. I can never get ahold of them, so I have to go there to order and then wait 20 minutes for my meal.
Best Thai food!  They have been here forever, but they always offer fresh, delicious food.
The food is always amazing and plentiful. The decorations are unique and quant. The servers are very cordial.

Roaches everywhere, enough said.

I'm a foodie, and ameture chef....and let me just tell you........The food is FANTASTIC!    A good friend of mine was married to a woman who was half Thai.   Her mother was from Thailand, and was trained there as a chef.   Everytime this friend of mine is in town we go to Siam Hut.    He knows Thai food well.   Well enough to converse with the owner about food that isnt on thier menu, she'll make for him a Thai specality called Lob (pronounced Lop) a salad of sorts with cilantro and lime juice, traditionally made with pork, however they make it for him with chicken, and it's fantastic!
